    "summary": "As a business and CX transformation expert, my mission is to empower companies to build a sustainable, customer-centric future. To achieve this, I blend expertise in consumer psychology and behaviour with the best change management practices. \n\nI believe in both the power of stories to energize us and of sound research to show us the way forward. Hence, I strive to share the stories I've encountered and sound evidence-based advice from academic research. \n\nMy interests in consumer psychology and customer experience have culminated in the publication of two books: \"The New Customer Experience Management\" (https://t.ly/-2xa6) and \"The Abusive Customer\" (https://t.ly/YYa6J). \n\nPersonally, I'm passionate about photography and I'm a devoted runner, with multiple half-marathons, a couple of full ones, and an ultra-marathon under my belt.\n\nI also had the honour of being a mentor in the second season of the Mentor the Young program (https://www.mentortheyoung.com/), supporting the development of bright young professionals. \n\nLet's connect over a cup of coffee and chat about transforming customer experience together.",
